wikipedia_page.main: James Storey (born 30 December 1929) is an English former footballer who played as a full back in the Football League for Exeter City, Rochdale and Darlington. He was also on the books of Newcastle United and Bournemouth & Boscombe Athletic without playing League football for either, and appeared in the Cheshire League for Macclesfield Town.
